<paragraph blockId="1.[97,749,1208,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis box="[136,392,1208,1232]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
History. – 
<taxonomicName box="[246,392,1208,1232]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">Lilium jankae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="KERNER, A." box="[587,749,1208,1232]" firstAuthor="KERNER" journalOrPublisher="Oesterr. Bot. Z." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="401 - 404" part="27" refId="ref2263" refString="KERNER, A. (1877). Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens. Oesterr. Bot. Z. 27: 401 - 404." title="Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens" type="journal article" year="1877">KERNER (1877)</bibRefCitation>
although Janka was the first who, several years earlier, noticed that this lily was somewhat different from species described thus far (
<bibRefCitation author="JANKA, V." box="[190,338,1305,1329]" firstAuthor="JANKA" journalOrPublisher="Oesterr. Bot. Z." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="273 - 274" part="18" refId="ref2238" refString="JANKA, V. (1868 b). Lilium pyrenaicum Baumg. Oesterr. Bot. Z. 18: 273 - 274." title="Lilium pyrenaicum Baumg" type="journal article" year="1868" yearSuffix="b">JANKA, 1868b</bibRefCitation>
). In 1868 Janka found this lily in Verespatak (Romania) while searching for 
<taxonomicName authority="Griseb." authorityName="Griseb." box="[513,749,1337,1361]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanicum">
<emphasis box="[513,660,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. albanicum</emphasis>
Griseb.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="JANKA, V." box="[106,264,1370,1394]" firstAuthor="JANKA" journalOrPublisher="Oesterr. Bot. Z." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="265 - 267" part="18" refId="ref2215" refString="JANKA, V. (1868 a). Correspondenz. Oesterr. Bot. Z. 18: 265 - 267." title="Correspondenz" type="journal article" year="1868" yearSuffix="a">JANKA, 1868a</bibRefCitation>
). Although the plants were already in fruits, after comparing them with the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[577,717,1402,1426]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanicum">
<emphasis box="[577,717,1402,1426]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. albanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
he concluded that they did not correspond with those of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.albanicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and that the plants best fit the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gouan" authorityName="Gouan" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrenaicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. pyrenaicum</emphasis>
Gouan
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="GRENIER, M. &amp; M. GODRON" box="[394,686,1499,1523]" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" refId="ref2066" refString="GRENIER, M. &amp; M. GODRON (1855). Fl. France 3. Paris." title="Fl. France 3" type="book" year="1855">GRENIER &amp; GORDON (1855)</bibRefCitation>
. Consequently he deduced that until close examination of flowering individuals would produce new evidence, the name 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrenaicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. pyrenaicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the plants from Verespatak should be used. Janka also states that he brought 50 bulbs from Verespatak with him in order to plant them in his garden and see them in flower to definitely determine the correct taxonomic status of this lily.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[98,749,1733,1951]" lastBlockId="1.[823,1475,276,1422]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Nine years later, 
<bibRefCitation author="KERNER, A." box="[308,468,1733,1757]" firstAuthor="KERNER" journalOrPublisher="Oesterr. Bot. Z." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="401 - 404" part="27" refId="ref2263" refString="KERNER, A. (1877). Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens. Oesterr. Bot. Z. 27: 401 - 404." title="Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens" type="journal article" year="1877">KERNER (1877)</bibRefCitation>
described the new species, which he names 
<taxonomicName box="[293,400,1765,1789]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[293,400,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in honour of Victor Janka. In Kerner’s personal herbarium at WU, we traced three herbarium sheets with plants collected by Janka in Verespatak under the name “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Baumg." authorityName="Baumg." box="[212,456,1862,1886]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrenaicum">
<emphasis box="[212,358,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.pyrenaicum</emphasis>
Baumg.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[462,469,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">/</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Heuff." authorityName="Heuff." box="[475,694,1862,1886]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albanicum">
<emphasis box="[475,609,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.albanicum</emphasis>
Heuff.
</taxonomicName>
” and revised by Kerner as 
<taxonomicName box="[318,414,1894,1918]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[318,414,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two of them, 
<emphasis box="[572,689,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<figureCitation box="[572,665,1894,1918]" captionStart="[" captionStartId="2.[113,119,1249,1269]" captionTargetBox="[114,1490,276,1202]" captionText="[Kerner s.n., WU] [© Universität Wien Herbarium. Reproduced with permission]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Kerner s</figureCitation>
.n.
</emphasis>
(WU [35591]) and 
<emphasis box="[245,367,1927,1951]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<figureCitation box="[245,342,1927,1951]" captionStart="[" captionStartId="2.[113,119,1249,1269]" captionTargetBox="[114,1490,276,1202]" captionText="[Kerner s.n., WU] [© Universität Wien Herbarium. Reproduced with permission]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Kerner s</figureCitation>
.n.
</emphasis>
(WU [35593]), have the collection date 
<date box="[876,1069,276,300]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1868-07-06" valueMax="1868-07-07" valueMin="1868-07-06">6 and 7 July 1868</date>
and are in fruit stage while one sheet has the collection date 
<date box="[1080,1228,308,332]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1869-06-19">19 June 1869</date>
and a fragment of the inflorescence is still present (
<emphasis box="[1128,1252,340,364]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<figureCitation box="[1128,1222,340,364]" captionStart="[" captionStartId="2.[113,119,1249,1269]" captionTargetBox="[114,1490,276,1202]" captionText="[Kerner s.n., WU] [© Universität Wien Herbarium. Reproduced with permission]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Kerner s</figureCitation>
.n.,
</emphasis>
WU [35592]). In the protologue 
<bibRefCitation author="KERNER, A." box="[950,1118,373,397]" firstAuthor="KERNER" journalOrPublisher="Oesterr. Bot. Z." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="401 - 404" part="27" refId="ref2263" refString="KERNER, A. (1877). Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens. Oesterr. Bot. Z. 27: 401 - 404." title="Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens" type="journal article" year="1877">KERNER (1877)</bibRefCitation>
states that some bulbs collected from Verespatak were sent by Janka to Innsbruck Botanical Garden where they flowered successfully. In WU, one sheet with the plant in flower, under the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1350,469,493]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[1257,1350,469,493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found and the herbarium label states: “Zwiebel aus Siebenbürgen, bei Verespatak von Janka gesammelt und mir nach Innsbruck gesandt. Blühte im bot. Garten in Innsbruck 
<date box="[1285,1380,565,589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" value="1876-06-06">6/6 1876</date>
. Kerner” (
<emphasis box="[833,965,597,621]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<figureCitation box="[833,934,597,621]" captionStart="[" captionStartId="2.[113,119,1249,1269]" captionTargetBox="[114,1490,276,1202]" captionText="[Kerner s.n., WU] [© Universität Wien Herbarium. Reproduced with permission]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Kerner s</figureCitation>
.n.,
</emphasis>
WU [35594]). Comparing the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[823,924,629,653]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[823,924,629,653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the before mentioned herbarium specimens it can be assumed that 
<bibRefCitation author="KERNER, A." box="[1037,1196,661,685]" firstAuthor="KERNER" journalOrPublisher="Oesterr. Bot. Z." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="401 - 404" part="27" refId="ref2263" refString="KERNER, A. (1877). Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens. Oesterr. Bot. Z. 27: 401 - 404." title="Die Vegetations-Verhaltnisse des mittleren und ostlichen Ungarns und angrenzenden Siebenburgens" type="journal article" year="1877">KERNER (1877)</bibRefCitation>
based his original description on both plants first collected by Janka in 1868 at Verespatak together with the plants growing at the Innsbruck Botanical Garden from bulbs collected by Janka. Therefore all mentioned specimens can be designated here as syntypes. Kerner also describes the distribution of this taxon, but without specifying the exact type locality: “In den mit hohen Gräsern und üppigen Stauden bewachsenen Schluchten unter dem Gipfel des Bohodei im Petrosaerzuge des Bihariagebirges und an der Ostgrenze des hier behandelten Gebietes auf den “Gaur” genannten Wiesen bei Verespatak.” In Kerner’s personal herbarium we also found specimens corresponding to his citation of the distribution in Biharia (Romania) and, although they are under the name 
<emphasis box="[1175,1278,1078,1102]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1274,1078,1102]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">L. jankae</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the collection date was not specified (
<emphasis box="[1021,1145,1110,1134]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<figureCitation box="[1021,1115,1110,1134]" captionStart="[" captionStartId="2.[113,119,1249,1269]" captionTargetBox="[114,1490,276,1202]" captionText="[Kerner s.n., WU] [© Universität Wien Herbarium. Reproduced with permission]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Kerner s</figureCitation>
.n.,
</emphasis>
WU [35589]; 
<emphasis box="[1299,1423,1110,1134]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<figureCitation box="[1299,1393,1110,1134]" captionStart="[" captionStartId="2.[113,119,1249,1269]" captionTargetBox="[114,1490,276,1202]" captionText="[Kerner s.n., WU] [© Universität Wien Herbarium. Reproduced with permission]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Kerner s</figureCitation>
.n.,
</emphasis>
WU [35590]). Therefore there is no direct evidence showing if particular specimen had been collected prior to the publication of the new species. However, there are several indications that those plants were also examined by Kerner while writing the original diagnosis and can be ascribed as syntypes. In the protologue he states that the plants growing at higher altitudes are shorter and with broader leaves, which corresponds to altitudes of Bohodei at Biharia (Romania) and to the appearance of herbarium specimens collected there by Kerner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[823,1475,1438,1622]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis box="[862,1273,1438,1462]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Taxonomic discussion. – 
<taxonomicName box="[1126,1273,1438,1462]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">Lilium jankae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName box="[824,983,1470,1494]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carniolicum">
<emphasis box="[824,983,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. carniolicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group which consists of seven European taxa belonging to sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1015,1083,1502,1526]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1083,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Lilium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ξ sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1468,1502,1526]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="154" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Liriotypus">
<emphasis box="[1175,1282,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Liriotypus</emphasis>
Asch. &amp; Graebn.
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="COMBER, H. F." box="[832,998,1534,1558]" firstAuthor="COMBER" journalOrPublisher="RHS Lily Yearb." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="86 - 105" part="13" refId="ref1984" refString="COMBER, H. F. (1949). A new classification of the genus Lilium. RHS Lily Yearb. 13: 86 - 105." title="A new classification of the genus Lilium" type="journal article" year="1949">COMBER, 1949</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="IKINCI, N. &amp; C. OBERPRIELER &amp; A. GUNER" box="[1010,1212,1534,1558]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="IKINCI" journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="647 - 656" part="36" refId="ref2137" refString="IKINCI, N., C. OBERPRIELER &amp; A. GUNER (2006). On the origin of European lilies: phylogenetic analysis of Lilium section Liriotypus using sequences of the nuclear ribosomal transcribed spacers. Willdenowia 36: 647 - 656." title="On the origin of European lilies: phylogenetic analysis of Lilium section Liriotypus using sequences of the nuclear ribosomal transcribed spacers" type="journal article" year="2006">IKINCI &amp; al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="RESETNIK, I. &amp; Z. LIBER &amp; Z. SATOVIC &amp; P. CIGIC &amp; T. NIKOLIC" box="[1224,1462,1534,1558]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="RESETNIK" journalOrPublisher="Pl. Syst. Evol." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="45 - 58" part="265" refId="ref2421" refString="RESETNIK, I., Z. LIBER, Z. SATOVIC, P. CIGIC &amp; T. NIKOLIC (2007). Molecular phylogeny and systematics of the Lilium carniolicum group (Liliaceae) based on nuclear ITS sequences. Pl. Syst. Evol. 265: 45 - 58." title="Molecular phylogeny and systematics of the Lilium carniolicum group (Liliaceae) based on nuclear ITS sequences" type="journal article" year="2007">REŠETNIK &amp; al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The relationships between the taxa in this group are still insufficiently understood and various taxonomic treatments exist.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[824,1475,1638,1950]" lastBlockId="2.[113,765,1375,1527]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
Recent molecular studies (
<bibRefCitation author="IKINCI, N. &amp; C. OBERPRIELER &amp; A. GUNER" box="[1155,1358,1638,1662]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="IKINCI" journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="647 - 656" part="36" refId="ref2137" refString="IKINCI, N., C. OBERPRIELER &amp; A. GUNER (2006). On the origin of European lilies: phylogenetic analysis of Lilium section Liriotypus using sequences of the nuclear ribosomal transcribed spacers. Willdenowia 36: 647 - 656." title="On the origin of European lilies: phylogenetic analysis of Lilium section Liriotypus using sequences of the nuclear ribosomal transcribed spacers" type="journal article" year="2006">IKINCI &amp; al., 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="RESETNIK, I. &amp; Z. LIBER &amp; Z. SATOVIC &amp; P. CIGIC &amp; T. NIKOLIC" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="RESETNIK" journalOrPublisher="Pl. Syst. Evol." pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="45 - 58" part="265" refId="ref2421" refString="RESETNIK, I., Z. LIBER, Z. SATOVIC, P. CIGIC &amp; T. NIKOLIC (2007). Molecular phylogeny and systematics of the Lilium carniolicum group (Liliaceae) based on nuclear ITS sequences. Pl. Syst. Evol. 265: 45 - 58." title="Molecular phylogeny and systematics of the Lilium carniolicum group (Liliaceae) based on nuclear ITS sequences" type="journal article" year="2007">REŠETNIK &amp; al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
) showed that 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1234,1670,1694]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[1127,1234,1670,1694]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch" authorityName="Koch" box="[824,1046,1702,1726]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carniolicum">
<emphasis box="[824,974,1702,1726]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.carniolicum</emphasis>
Koch
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Since" authorityName="L. Since" box="[1097,1383,1702,1726]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chalcedonicum">
<emphasis box="[1097,1281,1702,1726]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.chalcedonicum</emphasis>
L. Since
</taxonomicName>
detailed morphometric study including all members of 
<taxonomicName box="[1317,1467,1734,1758]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carniolicum">
<emphasis box="[1317,1467,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L.carniolicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is still lacking, the taxonomic conclusion remains uncertain and further research is required. However, most local floras, which cover the distribution range of 
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1358,1830,1854]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[1260,1358,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Romania, Bulgaria and Serbia) treat it as an independent species (
<bibRefCitation author="JANEV, A." editor="JORDANOV, D." firstAuthor="JANEV" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="247 - 254" part="2" refId="ref2182" refString="JANEV, A. (1964). Lilium. In: JORDANOV, D. &amp; al. (ed.), Fl. Bulgaria 2: 247 - 254." title="Lilium" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Fl. Bulgaria" year="1964">JANEV, 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="SAVULESCU, T. &amp; E. I. NYARADY" box="[891,1211,1894,1918]" firstAuthor="SAVULESCU" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="274 - 275" part="11" refId="ref2537" refString="SAVULESCU, T. &amp; E. I. NYARADY (1966). Fl. Romania 11: 274 - 275." title="Fl. Romania" type="journal article" year="1966">SÂVULESCU &amp; NYÁRÁDY, 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DIKLIC, N." box="[1222,1360,1894,1918]" editor="JOSIFOVIC, M." firstAuthor="DIKLIC" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" pagination="492 - 568" part="7" refId="ref2012" refString="DIKLIC, N. (1975). Liliaceae A. L. Juss. In: JOSIFOVIC, M. (ed.), Fl. Srbije 7: 492 - 568." title="Liliaceae A. L. Juss" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Srbije" year="1975">DIKLIĆ, 1975</bibRefCitation>
). Nonetheless, if one agrees that the taxon 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1274,1926,1950]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis box="[1175,1274,1926,1950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">L. jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is better treated at the subspecific level, as suggested by molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="RESETNIK, I. &amp; Z. LIBER &amp; Z. SATOVIC &amp; P. CIGIC &amp; T. NIKOLIC" journalOrPublisher="Pl. Syst. Evol." pageId="2" pageNumber="153" pagination="45 - 58" part="265" refId="ref2421" refString="RESETNIK, I., Z. LIBER, Z. SATOVIC, P. CIGIC &amp; T. NIKOLIC (2007). Molecular phylogeny and systematics of the Lilium carniolicum group (Liliaceae) based on nuclear ITS sequences. Pl. Syst. Evol. 265: 45 - 58." title="Molecular phylogeny and systematics of the Lilium carniolicum group (Liliaceae) based on nuclear ITS sequences" type="journal article" year="2007">REŠETNIK &amp; al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
), one have to accept the combination: 
<taxonomicName box="[113,445,1439,1463]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="carniolicum" subSpecies="jankae">
<emphasis box="[113,279,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">L. carniolicum</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[368,445,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">jankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[445,449,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="153">,</emphasis>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="ASCHERSON, P. &amp; P. GRAEBNER" journalOrPublisher="Leipzig" pageId="2" pageNumber="153" refId="ref1923" refString="ASCHERSON, P. &amp; P. GRAEBNER (1905 - 1907). Syn. Mitteleur. Fl. 3. Leipzig." title="Syn. Mitteleur. Fl. 3" type="book" year="1905">ASCHERSON &amp; GRAEBNER (1905-1907)</bibRefCitation>
, which gives priority to this epithet at the subspecific rank.
</paragraph>
